722310f-b.title: Manhattan: Park Avenue - 65th Street
722310f-b.text:
Park Avenue, east side, south from E. 87th to 65th Streets,
and showing prominently the Seventh Regiment Armory occunying the
67th -66th Street frontage. This structure, built in 1878-80
formerly had a pointed steeple where the flag is flying.. The
photographer is viewing same from a similar vantage point in both
instances (S.W. corner of Park Avenue and 88th Street) and shows
the changed railing used in fencfnm the center plot dividing the
traffic lanes.
June 8, 1028.
V1ee 2: April 25, 1238.
P.L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS
